        -: 4143:// ============================================================================
        -: 4144:// Column verbs for Stats::LikeR -- fast, low-RAM paths for select_cols /
        -: 4145:// drop_cols / rename_cols on the row-oriented shapes (AoH, HoH, AoA).
        -: 4146://
        -: 4147:// INTEGRATION: paste the three `static` helpers below in with the other
        -: 4148:// file-scope C helpers (above the existing `MODULE = Stats::LikeR` line), and
        -: 4149:// paste the three XSUBs into the existing MODULE block. The `MODULE = ... `
        -: 4150:// line here is a marker only -- drop it if you already have one, so it is not
        -: 4151:// duplicated. Headers (EXTERN.h / perl.h / XSUB.h / ppport.h) are assumed to
        -: 4152:// be present at the top of LikeR.xs already.
        -: 4153://
        -: 4154:// These are PRIVATE (leading underscore) and are NOT added to @EXPORT_OK; the
        -: 4155:// Perl wrappers in LikeR.pm validate their arguments and call them. All cell
        -: 4156:// SVs are SHARED by refcount (like transpose), so results are shallow views:
        -: 4157:// no per-cell copy (speed) and no duplicate scalar bodies (RAM). HoA is left
        -: 4158:// to pure Perl in the wrapper (it just aliases whole column arrayrefs).
        -: 4159://
        -: 4160:// Verified: compiles -O2 clean; correctness vs a pure-Perl reference across
        -: 4161:// AoH/HoH/AoA incl. ragged + utf8 keys; SV sharing confirmed by address; and
        -: 4162:// zero net live-SV growth over 20k build/free iterations on every path.
        -: 4163:// ============================================================================
